cs.SI, cs.DB, cs.CY, cs.SD, cs.HC 

The paper discusses the use of machine learning tools to analyze genealogy data, which involves data mining and database management (cs.DB). The study also involves social science research on ancestry and descent, which falls under the category of computational social science (cs.SI). The paper also mentions the use of third-party censuses to verify the accuracy of the data, which could fall under the category of data validation and verification (cs.CY). Additionally, the study involves analyzing population dynamics, which could fall under the categories of statistical analysis (cs.SD) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC) as the results could be used to inform user interfaces for genealogy websites.
